cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method to classify cardiac pathology based on image analysis and machine learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on the extraction of motion features from cine MRI images using a semi-supervised learning approach. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of explainable and flexible models for pathology classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of image-derived features and motion characterization further suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
